PREREQUISITES
 apt-get install php5-adodb php5-mcrypt libphp-adodb
 a2enmod rewrite

INSTALLATION
Add as submodule to your project:
git submodule add LOCATION/web_framework

Add minimal links:
 - mkdir -p htdocs includes views/templates
 - cd htdocs && ln -s ../web_framework/htdocs/index.php .

Set htaccess for htdocs
 - mkdir -p data
 - cp web_framework/templates/htaccess-* data
 - Edit for content!
 - htpasswd -c -s .htpasswd XXX
 - cd htdocs && ln -s ../data/htacces-XXX .htaccess
 - Add to .gitignore if needed

Make config file:
 - cp web_framework/templates/default_config.php includes/config.php
 - Add to .gitignore if needed
 - Edit the config file!
 
Make DB if needed:
 - mysql -u root -p mysql
   grant all on XXXX.* to 'XXXX'@'localhost' identified by 'XXXX';

Make a default frame if needed:
 - cp web_framework/templates/default_frame.inc.php includes

Make first hello world page:
 - 

Add apache config
 - cp web_framework/templates/apache_site_conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/XXXXX
 - Edit the file
 - cd /etc/apache2/sites-enables && ln -s ../sites-available/XXXXX
 - /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
